        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 2. Collapsible Callout\n",
        "\n",
        "Quarto callouts can be made collapsible with `collapse=\"true\"`. They start folded\n",
        "and expand on click.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note collapse=\"true\"}\n",
        "## 📝 Click to expand this note\n",
        "\n",
        "This content is hidden until you click the title. Callouts support full Markdown\n",
        "inside them, including lists and code:\n",
        "\n",
        "- First hidden point\n",
        "- Second hidden point\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "print(\"Even code blocks work inside a collapsed callout\")\n",
        "```\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-tip collapse=\"true\"}\n",
        "## 💡 A folded tip\n",
        "\n",
        "Use `collapse=\"false\"` (the default for some types) to have them open initially.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 3. Raw HTML `<details>` Fold\n",
        "\n",
        "For arbitrary collapsible content, drop straight into HTML. This works in any\n",
        "HTML output and is the most flexible option.\n",
        "\n",
        "<details>\n",
        "<summary>🔽 Click to reveal arbitrary content</summary>\n",
        "\n",
        "This block is a native browser `<details>` element. You can put **any** Markdown\n",
        "or HTML here — tables, images, math, etc.\n",
        "\n",
        "| Column A | Column B |\n",
        "|----------|----------|\n",
        "| 1        | 2        |\n",
        "| 3        | 4        |\n",
        "\n",
        "</details>\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 4. Images\n",
        "\n",
        "### Remote image\n",
        "\n",
        "A standard Markdown image pulled from the web, with a caption and sizing:\n",
        "\n",
        "![The Quarto logo](https://quarto.org/quarto.png){width=300 fig-alt=\"Quarto logo\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "### Generated image (folded code)\n",
        "\n",
        "The code that produces this plot is folded; only the resulting image shows by\n",
        "default."
      ],
      "id": "322da881"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| code-fold: true\n",
        "#| code-summary: \"👉 Show the plotting code\"\n",
        "#| fig-cap: \"A simple sine wave generated with matplotlib\"\n",
        "\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "x = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 200)\n",
        "y = np.sin(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 3))\n",
        "plt.plot(x, y, color=\"#89b4fa\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"sin(x)\")\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
